vertices.label: male given name
vertices.description: given name usually meant for boys and men

vertices.label: Charles
vertices.description: name: given name and family name

vertices.label: Latin script
vertices.description: writing system used to write most Western, Northern and Central European languages

properties.label: part of
properties.description: object of which the subject is a part (if this subject is already part of object A which is a part of object B, then please only make the subject part of object A), inverse property of "has part" (P527, see also "has parts of the class" (P2670))

properties.label: name day
properties.description: day of the year associated with a first/given name. A qualifier should be used to identify the calendar that is being used. Distinguish from "feast day" (P:P841)

properties.label: instance of
properties.description: that class of which this subject is a particular example and member; different from P279 (subclass of); for example: K2 is an instance of mountain; volcano is a subclass of mountain (and an instance of volcanic landform)

properties.label: writing system
properties.description: alphabet, character set or other system of writing used by a language, word, or text, supported by a typeface

properties.label: language of work or name
properties.description: language associated with this creative work (such as books, shows, songs, broadcasts or websites) or a name (for persons use "native language" (P103) and "languages spoken, written or signed" (P1412))

properties.label: family name identical to this given name
properties.description: last name that is the same as a given first name. Use on items for given names

properties.label: given name version for other gender
properties.description: equivalent name (with respect to the meaning of the name) in the same language: female version of a male first name, male version of a female first name. Add primarily the closest matching one

properties.label: said to be the same as
properties.description: this item is said to be the same as that item, though this may be uncertain or disputed
